The paper deals with privacy-preserving search, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of Locality Sensitive Hashing (LSH) for sub-linear near-neighbor search, which is a technique commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of probabilistic embeddings and multi-party computation, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CY).
